            , haberdashers; Mason, gauze-weaver; and another; who all gave him an extraordinary good character.</p>
               <p>Court. You cannot carry character further.</p>
               <p>Mr. Graham. We have many more.</p>
               <p>Court. Call 
               <persName id="t17880507-57-person546">
                  John
                   Payne
               <interp inst="t17880507-57-person546" type="surname" value="Payne"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17880507-57-person546" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17880507-57-person546" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>Mr. Graham. He was not present.</p>
               <p>The Jury retired for above an hour, and returned with a verdict,</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17880507-57-verdict274" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17880507-57-verdict274" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               NOT GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Tried by the London Jury before Mr. RECORDER.</p>
            </div1>
